  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If `hit.hierarchy.lvl1` is an array, and you want to display every item of the array, what you do is you replace:\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\n<Highlight hit={hit} attribute=\"hierarchy.lvl1\" />\r\n```\r\n\r\nwith\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\n{hit.hierarchy.lvl1.map((_, i) => <Highlight key={i} hit={hit} attribute={[\"hierarchy\", \"lvl1\", i]} />}\r\n```\r\n\r\nso that you are looping over the items in the array, and create a highlight for each of the items in the array, this is similar to doing `hierarchy.lvl1[i]`\r\n ",
    "created_at": "2023-08-02T09:01:35Z",
